quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  3,113,"They are not all alike. Of the people of the Book there is a nation upright, reciting God's signs throughout the night, as they adore the while"
  3,114,"They believe in God, and in the last day, and bid what is reasonable, and forbid what is wrong, and vie in charity; these are among the righteous"
  3,115,"What ye do of good surely God will not deny, for God knows those who fear"
  3,116,"Verily, those who misbelieve, their wealth is of no service to them, nor their children either, against God; they are the fellows of the Fire, and they shall dwell therein for aye"
  3,117,"The likeness of what they expend in this life of the world, is as the likeness of wind wherein is a cold blast that falls upon a people's tilth who have wronged themselves and destroys it. It is not God who wrongs them, but it is themselves they wrong"
  3,118,"O ye who believe! take not to intimacy with others than yourselves; they will not fail to spoil you; they would fain ye came to trouble,- hatred is shown by their mouths; but what their breasts conceal is greater still. We have made manifest to you our signs, did ye but understand"
  3,119,"Ye it is who love them, but they love not you; and ye believe in the Book, all of it. But when they meet you they say, 'We believe;' and when they go aside they bite their finger tips at you through rage. Say, 'Die in your rage, for God doth know the nature of men's breasts"
  3,120,"If good luck touch you it is bad for them, but if bad luck befall you they rejoice therein; yet if ye are patient and fear, their tricks shall not harm you, for what they do God comprehends"
  3,121,When thou didst set forth early from thy people to settle for the believers a camp to fight;- but God both hears and knows
  3,122,"when two companies of you were on the point of showing cowardice; but God was their guardian, for on God surely the believers do rely"
  3,123,"Why! God gave you victory at Bedr when ye were in a poor way; fear God, then, haply ye may give thanks"
  3,124,"When thou didst say unto the believers, 'Is it not enough for you that your Lord assists you with three thousand of the angels sent down from on high"
  3,125,"Yea, if ye are patient and fear God, and they come upon you on a sudden, now, your Lord will assist you with five thousand of His angels, (angels) of mark"
  3,126,"God only made this as glad tidings for you to comfort your hearts withal,- for victory is but from God, the mighty, the wise"
  3,127,"to cut off the flank of those who misbelieve, or make them downcast, that they may retire disappointed"
  3,128,"Thou hast nothing to do with the affair at all, whether He turn towards them again or punish them; for, verily, they are unjust"
  3,129,"God's is what is in the heavens and in the earth. He forgives whom He pleases, and punishes whom He pleases; for God is forgiving and merciful"
  3,130,"O ye who believe! devour not usury doubly doubled, but fear God, perchance ye may be prosperous"
  3,131,fear the fire which is prepared for the unbelievers
  3,132,"and obey God and His Apostle, perchance ye may get mercy"